(25, 1, 15, '', 'GST Annual Return', 'GST Annual Return Filing (GSTR-9)', 'GSTR-9 or GST annual return filing for taxpayers registered under GST Scheme.', 'GSTR-9 or GST annual return filing for regular taxpayers registered under GST not requiring Audit.', 'GSTR-9 or GST annual return filing for regular taxpayers registered under GST along with GST audit.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	How to File GST Annual Return for 2021</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Implemented in India from 1st July 2017. Over 1.3 crore businesses in India have been registered and issued GST registration under the new GST regime. The entities registered under GST must file annual returns as per the scheduled GST return due date.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GST annual return filing is mandatory for all entities with a turnover of more than two crores required to obtain GST registration, irrespective of the business activity or sales or profitability during the return filing period. Hence, even a dormant business that gets GST registration must file GST returns.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.68421em; font-size: 1.35714em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	What is GSTR 9: Annual Return Filing?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GSTR 9 is the annual return that is to be to be filed yearly by the taxpayers registered under GST.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GSTR 9 is to be filed yearly by the taxpayers registered under GST. It consists of details regarding the outward and the inward supplies made during the relevant financial year.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Before filing GSTR 9, the taxpayer must file all GSTR-1, GSTR-3B, or GSTR 4 returns. In case of over dues, the GSTR registration holder will not be allowed to file an annual GST annual return.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GSTR 9 consists of details regarding the outward and the inward supplies made or received during the relevant financial year under CGST, SGST, and IGST. It is a consolidation of all the monthly/quarterly returns filed in that year.</p>\r\n', 2899, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Turnover less than Rs.25 lakhs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		GSTR-9 Filing</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Personalised GST Accountant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Turnover less than Rs.2 crores</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		GSTR-9 Filing</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Personalised GST Accountant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 8899, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Turnover more than Rs.2 crores</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		GSTR-9 Filing</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		GSTR-9C Filing</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Personalised GST Accountant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '02-02-2022-12-13-38-pmGST-ANNUAL-RETURN.jpg', 1, 4899, '<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who should file GSTR 9?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 10px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	All taxpayers/taxable persons registered under GST must file their GSTR 9. However, the following are NOT required to file GSTR 9:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-40\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 40px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Taxpayers opting composition scheme (They must file&nbsp;GSTR-9A)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Casual Taxable Person</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Input service distributors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Non-resident taxable persons</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Persons paying&nbsp;TDS&nbsp;under section 51 of CGST Act.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	GST Annual Return Due Date</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-40\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 40px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The due date for filing Form GSTR-9 (Annual Return) and Form GSTR-9C (Reconciliation Statement) for financial year 2019-2020 has been extended up to 31st March 2021 basing the pandemic situation.The Government has also decided to simplify these forms by making various fields of these forms is optional.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	What details are required to be filled in the GSTR-9?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The GSTR-9 is broadly divided into six parts and 19 sections. Each part asks for the details that are readily available from previously filed returns and books of accounts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	This form asks for disclosure of annual sales, bifurcating between the cases subjected to tax and those not subjected to Tax.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The annual value of the inward supplies and ITC availed thereon is to be revealed.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Further, these purchases have to be classified as inputs, input services, and capital goods. Details of ITC that need to be reversed due to ineligibility are to be entered.</p>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who should file GSTR-9A?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-20\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 20px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GST registered taxpayer who has opted for composition scheme under the GST Act are required to file GSTR-9A. GSTR-9A includes all the information that is submitted by the taxpayer, furnished in the quarterly return during a specific fiscal year.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Eligibility</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 10px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Every taxpayer registered under the composition levy scheme under GST must file GSTR-9A. However, the following individuals are not required to file GSTR-9A:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-40\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 40px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Input Service Distributor</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Non-resident taxable individuals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Individuals who pay Tax deducted at sources (TDS) under Section 51 of the Income Tax Act.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Casual Taxable Individuals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		E-commerce operators who pay Tax collected at source (TCS) under Section 52 of the Income Tax Act.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who should file GSTR-9C?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-20\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 20px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Form GSTR 9C is meant for filing the reconciliation statement of taxpayers about a particular financial year. The form is a statement of reconciliation between the Annual Returns in GSTR-9&nbsp;and the figures mentioned in the taxpayer&#39;s Audited Financial Statements. Given that, this CA-certified form must be filed during the filing of Annual Returns in GSTR-9 and the Audited Financial Statements. The obligation can either be completed through the GST portal or a Facilitation Centre. This article deals with the usage and need of the form.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Eligibility</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GSTR 9C applies to taxpayers who are required to obtain an annual GST audit of their accounts. It must be prepared and certified by a Chartered Accountant or Cost Accountant.</p>\r\n', 'gst-annual-return', 'GST Annual Return Filing (GSTR-9)', 'Taxpayers should file GST returns on the 10th, 15th and 20th of each month.  Taxpayer must still log in to the GST portal and file NIL GST return to avoid penalty in case of no business activity or transaction during a month.', 'GST Annual Return Filing (GSTR-9), gst annual return, gst annual return due date, gst annual return due date for fy 2021, gst annual return extension, annual return gst, GST Annual Return Filing in vellore, gstr 9 due date, gstr 9c, gst annual return due date, gst annual return, gst audit due date, gstr 9c due date, gstr 9 last date, gstr 4 annual return, annual return gst, gstr 9c annual return due date, gstr 9a, gstr 9 form, gstr 9 and 9c, gst audit last date, gstr9 and gstr9c, gstr 9 and 9c due date, annual return for composition dealer, gst annual return last date, gstr 9 annual return, due date for gstr 9, annual return under gst, gstr 9 pdf, gstr 9c filing due date, gstr 9b, gst annual return limit, gstr 9 filing, due date of gstr 9, last date of gstr 9, gstr 9c last date, gst annual return date, gst audit date, annual return gst due date, gstr 9 & 9c, gst r9, gstr 9 c, gstr 9a due date, form gstr 9, gstr 9 mandatory, gstr 9 date, gstr 9c filing, annual return gstr 9 due date, annual return in gst, gst annual return form, gstr 9c form, gstr 9 form pdf, gstr9 limit, gstr 9 annual return due date, due date of gst annual return, gst annual return for composition dealer, due date gstr 9, 9c due date, gstr 9a and 9c, gstr 9 & 9c due date, gstr 9 filing turnover limit, annual return gst last date, gst yearly return, gstr 9 filing date, annual return gstr 9, gst composition annual return due date, last date for gstr 9, last date of gst annual return, gstr 9 offline utility, gstr 9 9c, 9c gst return, annual return of gst, annual gst return for composition dealer, last date gstr 9, gstr 9 return due date, gstr 9 filing due date, form gstr 9c, due date of gst audit, annual gst, gst r9 last date, composition dealer annual return, gstr 9 return, composition scheme annual return, due date for gst audit, due date of filing annual return under gst, last date for filing gstr 9, gst annual return filing date, 9c in gst, due date of annual return of gst, form gstr 9 pdf, last date of gst audit, filing of gstr 9, gstr 9 utility, gst annual, due date for gst annual return, gst composition annual return, yearly gst return, gstr 9 9a 9b 9c, gstr 9 filing limit, due date for filing gstr 9, annual return for composition scheme, last date to file gstr 9, gst annual filing due date, gstr 4 annual return offline utility, turnover for gstr 9, gstr 9 a, last date for gst annual return, form 9c in gst, gstr 9 and 9c last date, due date for gstr 9c, limit for filing gstr 9, gstr 9 rules, gst composition scheme annual return, gstr 9c return due date, gstr 9b due date, last date of filing gstr 9, gst audit and annual return book pdf, gstr 9 filing last date, download gstr 2a for whole year, gst composition annual return last date, form 9a gst, gst return annual return due date, due date for filing annual return under gst, about gstr 9, about gstr 9c, annual return for composition, gst annual return mandatory, gstr 9 is mandatory, annual return gst limit, annual return for gst composition dealer, all about gstr 9, annual return gstr 4, gstr 9a meaning, gst form 9 and 9c, late filing of gstr 9, gst return 9 and 9c, annual return of composition dealer, types of gst annual return, gst form 9c, gstr 9 download, filing gstr 9c, last date for gst audit, annual gstr 2a download, composition gst annual return, gstr 09, gstr 9 9a 9c, gst due date annual return, gstr 9c mandatory, gstr 9a filing, gstr 9a last date, gstr 4 annual return filing, last date gst annual return, gst annual return requirement, gstr 9 audit due date, annual return composition, gst annual return 9c, due date of gstr 9c, gst annual filing, 9c gst last date, gst annual return filing due date, gstr 09 due date, gstr 9 for composition dealers, gstr 9a for composition dealers, gstr 9 offline utility download, gst return 9, gstr 9 return filing, gstr 9 excel utility, annual return for gst, gst r9 due date, about gstr 9a, gstr form 9, filing gstr 9, gstr 9c audit, limit for gst annual return, gstr 9a annual return, gstr 9 audit limit, gst audit 9c due date, gst due date for gstr 9, annual gst return last date, form 9c gst, gstr 9 pdf download, last date for filing gst annual return, gstr 9 youtube, gstr 9 in excel, gstr 9 return last date, gstr 9 and 9c limit, annual return for composition dealer under gst, due date for filing gstr 9 and 9c, gst return 9c, annual return under gst for composition dealer, date of filing annual return in gst, due date for gstr 9 and 9c, last date of gstr 9c, last date annual return gst, gst annual return gstr 9c, annual return 9 and 9c, gstr 9 due, gstr 9 for composition scheme, gstr9 filling, about gstr 9 and 9c, gstr 9 annual return last date, smart filings,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(26, 1, 15, '', 'GST Registration for Foreigners', 'GST Registration for Foreigners', 'GST registration as non-resident taxable person.', 'GST registration as non-resident taxable person with 1 year GST return filing.', 'GST registration as a non-resident taxable person with 1 year GST return filing, Authorized person in India, virtual office.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	What is GST registration for foreigners?</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GST registration for foreigners is necessary for the non-resident taxable persons who are making taxable supplies in India. With India emerging as an economic powerhouse, a lot of non-resident Indias are willing to set up business in India. Hence, a non-resident taxable person has to apply for GST registration if he is undertaking transactions involving the supply of goods or services or both.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Hence, an individual who is staying abroad or a foreign business or an organization that is supplying foods or services in India is considered as a Non-resident taxable person who has to comply with all the regulations under the Goods and Service Law Act. The non-resident taxable person must appoint a nominee in India who can undertake the compliances on their behalf in accordance with the GST regulations. GST registration by the foreigners is to be obtained 5 days before commencing with the business.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"lead\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 400;\">\r\n	Why GST registration?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Goods and Services Tax Act was introduced by the Indian government, to subsume different types of taxes levied at the Central or State level such as Service Tax, Luxury Tax, VAT, entertainment tax, etc, and a consolidated structure is offered under the GST Act. Here, a non-resident India who undertakes transactional activities that are relevant to services and goods should also register as a taxable person under GST.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Goods and Service Tax Law has improved the ease of doing business. The complexities of tax have reduced as the GST has subsumed multiple taxes into a single simple system.</p>\r\n', 9899, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Non-Resident GST Registration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Non-Resident GST Registration</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		1 Year Authorised Signatory</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border: none; line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		1 Year Place of Business Address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 79899, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Non-Resident GST Registration</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		1 Year Authorised Signatory</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		1 Year Place of Business Address</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border: none; line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		GSTR-5 Return Filing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '02-02-2022-12-15-14-pmGST-REG-FOR-FOREIGNERS.jpg', 1, 29899, '<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	What are the documents required to obtain the GST registration?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	GST registration for a non-resident taxable person requires the submission of the following documents.</p>\r\n<ul class=\"timeline m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: none; position: relative; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important;\">\r\n	<li class=\"timeline-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 3rem 2rem 3rem 5rem; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"timeline-icon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 5px; background-color: rgb(34, 80, 252); position: absolute; border-radius: 50%; left: 0px; width: 34px; height: 34px; z-index: 3; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; font-size: 18px;\">\r\n			1</div>\r\n		<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n			Principal place of business proof</h3>\r\n		<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">For own business-</span>&nbsp;Any document that is supporting the ownership of the premise like the latest tax property or the municipal khata or the copy of the electricity bill.</li>\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">For rented or leased premises-</span>&nbsp;A copy of the valid rent or lease agreement with any document that is supporting the ownership of the lessor&#39;s premises like the property tax receipt or municipal khata copy or the electricity bill.</li>\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">For premises not covered above-</span>&nbsp;A copy of the consent letter with a document supporting the ownership of the consenter&#39;s premises like the municipal khata or the electricity bill copy. Even for shared properties, the same documents can be uploaded.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"timeline-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 3rem 2rem 3rem 5rem; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"timeline-icon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 5px; background-color: rgb(34, 80, 252); position: absolute; border-radius: 50%; left: 0px; width: 34px; height: 34px; z-index: 3; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; font-size: 18px;\">\r\n			2</div>\r\n		<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n			Identity Proof</h3>\r\n		<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; letter-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n			It is necessary to submit the scanned copy of the passport of the Non-resident taxable person with the VISA details. In the case of a business entity that is incorporated or established outside India the application for the registration, it should be submitted along with the tax identification number or the unique number that is based on which the entity is identified by the government of that country or the PAN if it is available.</p>\r\n		<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				In the case of the Company/ Society / LLC/ FCNR etc, a person holding the attorney power with the authorization certificate.</li>\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				A scanned copy of the incorporation certificate of the company is registered outside India or in the country.</li>\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				Scanned copy of the license that is issued by the foreign country if it is available.</li>\r\n			<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				Scanned copy of the clearance certificate that is issued by the Government of India, if available.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"timeline-item\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 3rem 2rem 3rem 5rem; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<div class=\"timeline-icon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 5px; background-color: rgb(34, 80, 252); position: absolute; border-radius: 50%; left: 0px; width: 34px; height: 34px; z-index: 3; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-align: center; font-size: 18px;\">\r\n			3</div>\r\n		<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n			Bank Account proof</h3>\r\n		<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; letter-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n			Scanned copy of the first page of the bank passbook or one page of the bank statement, the opening page of the bank passbook held in the name of the business that contains the Account number, name of the account holder, MICR, IFSC code, and branch details.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Eligibility Criteria</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who can register as a non-resident taxpayer under GST in India?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Irrespective of the turnover a non-resident taxable person is required to obtain GST registration in India. Here it should be noted that all the non-resident taxpayers are required to obtain the GST registration five days before commencing with the business activity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	It is better if the foreign business that is supplying the goods and services gets the GST registration at the earliest. It is to be noted that the NRI cannot exercise the option to pay taxes under the composition scheme.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	A business entity that is incorporated or established outside India that is making the supply of taxable goods and services is required to obtain the GST registration in India his tax identification number will be based on the country.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center;\">\r\n	Benefits of obtaining GST registration</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	What are the benefits of getting GST registration?</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-25\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 25px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">Unified taxation system:</span>&nbsp;GST registration is a unified platform that has subsumed all the other taxes such as the VAT registration, service tax registrations. All indirect taxes are streamlined under one umbrella GST registration.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">Ease of doing business:</span>&nbsp;There are multiple taxes such as the Central Sales Tax, Additional Custom duty, purchase tax, luxury tax. etc anymore as the GST undertakes the taxes on the goods and services. This has made business easier for the taxpayers.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">Decreased tax liability:</span>&nbsp;With a greater annual turnover threshold the taxes which need to be paid are lower as compared to what was in the case of the VAT. GST has also increased the tax base considerably which decreased the overall tax liability and made business more compliant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	Important Instructions to be followed by the taxpayers applying for GST registration for foreigners</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The name of the applicant must be entered as per the passport.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The applicant must apply for GST registration on the common portal by filing form GST REG-09 at least five days before the business&#39;s commencement.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Tax identification number / unique number (number by which the respective government identifies the entity) or PAN (if applicable) is necessary to be submitted along with the application in case of a business entity incorporated or established outside India.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The application must be duly signed or verified through EVC.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'gst-registration-for-foreigners', 'GST Registration for Foreigners', 'GST Registration for Foreigners File India with smartFilings. Also, Find step-by-step guide for GST Filing online process in GST Portal and documents required, due dates, penalty & Interest on GST Returns.', 'GST Registration for Foreigners, gst registration for foreign company, gst registration for foreigners, gst registration foreigners, Gst Registration Foreigners in vellore, smart filings, ', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL);
