list-style: none; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(45, 44, 44);\">\r\n		Details of Previous Profit and Loss Account and Balance Sheet (if any)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(45, 44, 44);\">\r\n		Latest Address / ID of Designated Partners</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(45, 44, 44);\">\r\n		Valid Digital Signature of Designated partners</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(45, 44, 44);\">\r\n		Valid Email ID and Phone number of Designated partners</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style: none; line-height: 1.5rem; color: rgb(45, 44, 44);\">\r\n		OTP for Email / Phone validation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Income Tax Rate for LLP</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The income tax rate applicable for LLPs registered in India is 30% of the total income. Besides the income tax, a surcharge is levied on the income of the tax payable at the rate of 12% when the total income is exceeding Rs.1 crore.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Health &amp; Education Cess</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Health and Education cess of 4% is applicable on the&nbsp;amount of income tax and the applicable surcharge.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Minimum Alternate Tax (MAT) for LLP</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Similar to income tax applicable for a company, LLP is also subject to minimum alternate tax. A minimum alternate tax of 18.5% of adjusted total income is applicable for LLP. Hence, income tax payable by LLP cannot be less than 18.5 percent (increased by income tax surcharge, education cess, and secondary and higher education cess).</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	LLPs Involved in International Transaction</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	LLPs that entered into an international transaction with associated enterprises or undertook certain Specified Domestic Transactions are required to file Form 3CEB. Form 3CEB must be certified by a Chartered Accountant. LLPs required to file Form 3CEB have 3oth November as the deadline for LLP tax filing.</p>\r\n', 'llp', 'Annual Compliance - LLP', 'LLPs in India must file MCA annual return and income tax return each year. Failure to file MCA or tax return to lead to penalty and disqualification of Partners.', 'LLP Annual Filing, MCA Annual Filing , Form 8 LLP, Form 11 LLP, LLP Tax Audit, LLP Accounting, LLP Compliance, LLP compliance in vellore, smart filings, form 8 llp, form 11 llp, llp annual filing, form 8 llp due date, form 11 llp due date, llp annual compliance, due date of form 11 llp, due date for form 11 llp, llp annual return, due date of form 8 llp, form 8 and form 11 of llp, llp roc compliance, due date for form 8 llp, form 11 for llp, llp annual filing due date, llp roc filing due date, due date for llp form 11, llp annual return form, annual compliance of llp, llp roc filing, due date of llp form 11, llp annual return due date, form 11 roc, due date of filing form 8 llp, roc form 11 due date, last date for filing form 11 of llp, due date of filing form 11 llp, form 8 and form 11 of llp due date, llp annual filing forms, due date for filing form 8 and form 11 of llp, last date for filing form 8 of llp, llp annual compliance cost, form 11 llp last date, llp annual return filing due date, form 11 of llp due date, llp financial year, last date of filing form 8 llp, last date to file form 8 llp, llp filing last date, form 8 of llp due date, llp form 8 last date, due date for filing llp form 8, form 8 llp last date, llp annual forms, due date for filing form 11 llp, due date for filing form 8 llp, llp form 8 and 11, form 8 and 11 of llp, last date of form 11 llp, form 11 for llp due date, llp annual compliance due date, form 8 & 11 llp, llp annual return last date, llp form 11 last date, last date for form 8 llp, annual return of llp due date, roc forms for llp, due date for filing llp form 11, last date for llp form 11, last date of form 8 of llp, llp form 8 and form 11 due date, last date for filing llp form 8, last date for filing llp form 11, form 8 for llp due date, due date of llp annual filing, annual filing of llp with roc, annual forms for llp, llp form 8 filing due date, ', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(33, 1, 16, '', 'Foreign Subsidiary', 'Annual Compliance - Foreign Subsidiary', 'Annual return filing, income tax return filing, secretarial services, compliance management for foreign subsidiary company with a turnover of less than Rs.10 lakhs per annum.', 'Annual return filing, income tax return filing, secretarial services, compliance management for foreign subsidiary company with a turnover of less than Rs.50 lakhs per annum.', 'Annual return filing, income tax return filing, secretarial services, compliance management for foreign subsidiary company with a turnover of less than Rs.100 lakhs per annum.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	Foreign Subsidiary Company Compliance</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	A company where 50% or more of its equity shares are owned by a foreign company is a foreign subsidiary company. The foreign company in such case is called the holding company or the parent company.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Compliances are based on the company that is incorporated. Hence, it is necessary to understand what compliances are supposed to be met according to the type of the company, the operations of the industry, annual turnover, number of employees, etc.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Foreign subsidiary companies are mandatorily required to maintain compliance according to the Income Tax Act, Companies Act, Transfer pricing guidelines, and FEMA guidelines.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The foreign subsidiary compliance includes income tax filing with the income tax department, annual return with the ministry of corporate affairs, and other filings with the authorities like the Reserve Bank of India or the securities and exchange board of India (SEBI).</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	All the companies even foreign subsidiaries will have to comply with other Indian tax regulations like the TDS, GST regulation, PF regulation, ESI regulations, and others. The compliance requirement for a foreign subsidiary company would differ based on the industry, state of incorporation, number of employees, and sales turnover.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Foreign Direct Investment of up to 100% is allowed into an Indian private limited company and limited company for most of the sector. The amount of FDI in India has increased manifold over the last few years due to a booming economy and welcoming environment for foreign investors</p>\r\n', 59899, 'Annual Return Filing, Income Tax Return Filing, Secretarial Services, Compliance Management For Foreign Subsidiary Company With A Turnover Of Less Than Rs.10 Lakhs Per Annum.', 'Annual Return Filing, Income Tax Return Filing, Secretarial Services, Compliance Management For Foreign Subsidiary Company With A Turnover Of Less Than Rs.50 Lakhs Per Annum.', 99899, 'Annual Return Filing, Income Tax Return Filing, Secretarial Services, Compliance Management For Foreign Subsidiary Company With A Turnover Of Less Than Rs.100 Lakhs Per Annum.', '02-02-2022-12-26-11-pmforeign-subsidiary.jpg', 1, 69899, '<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Name and address of the foreign investor(s);</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Date of receipt of funds and the Rupee equivalent;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Name and address of the authorized dealer through whom the funds have been received;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Details of the Government approval, if any; and</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		KYC report (Identify and Address proof) on the non-resident investor from the overseas bank remitting the amount of consideration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	FDI Inflow into the Company</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	What is the role of FDI in a foreign subsidiary company?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	An Indian Company that issues shares or convertible debentures under the FDI can receive the money for such shares or debentures through the following modes:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Remittance through normal banking channels.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Debit to NRE/FCNR account of a person concerned maintained with a Bank.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Conversion of royalty/lump sum/ technical know-how fee due for payment or conversion of ECB shall be treated as consideration for issue of shares.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Conversion of import payables/pre-incorporation expenses/share swap can be treated as consideration for the issue of shares with the approval of FIPB.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Debit to non-interest bearing Escrow account in Indian Rupees in India which is opened with the approval from AD Category &ndash; I bank and is maintained with the AD Category I bank on behalf of residents and non-residents towards payment of share purchase consideration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'foreign-subsidiary', 'Annual Compliance - Foreign Subsidiary', 'List of all private limited company compliance, 2021 due dates and non-compliance penalty. Private limited companies registered in India must file their annual return (MGT-7 and AOC-4), income tax return, INC-22A and DIN eKYC for the Directors.', 'Annual Compliance - Foreign Subsidiary, Compliance for a Private Limited Company, annual compliance for company, annual compliance for llp, annual compliance for opc at lowest price, Annual Compliance for Private Limited Company, annual compliance for private limited company as per companies act 2013, annual compliance for private limited company under companies act 2013, annual compliance for public limited company, annual compliance for pvt ltd company, annual compliance of company, annual compliance of llp, annual compliance of private company, annual compliance of private limited company, annual compliance package, Annual Compliance Private Limited Company Online, annual compliances for private limited company, annual compliances of a private limited company, annual compliances of private limited company, annual filing last date, Annual Return Filing, annual roc compliance for private limited companies, Audit Requirements for Private Limited Companies, board meetings of private company, Can auditor be appointed for more than 5 years, Can I use money from my business account for personal use, Company Annual Compliance for Startups, comp