(34, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-1 Return', 'Personal Tax Return Filing ITR-1', 'Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of less than Rs.5 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 1 Filing Form</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Income Tax Department has categorized the taxpayers into the group to ease the tax compliances this categorization is done based on the income and the sources of the income. ITR 1 Return filing in India is for people with an income of up to Rs.50 lakh.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	This article is a comprehensive guide to understand the ITR 1 Sahaj Form. Each category of the taxpayer has to compute the taxable income as it is laid down in the Income Tax Act,1961. Post computation it is necessary for the taxpayer to file the Income Tax Returns.</p>\r\n', 488, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of less than Rs.5 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', 2488, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for an individual with salary income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-27-07-pmITR-1.jpg', 1, 988, '<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Form 16</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Salary slips</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Interest Certificates from the Post offices and Banks</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Form 16A/16B/16C</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Form 26AS</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Tax saving investment proof</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction under the Section 80 D to 80 U</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Home Loan statement from the NBFC or the Bank</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Capital Gains.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who can file ITR 1 Sahaj Form?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 1 Sahaj Form is for individuals that have income up to Rs.50 lakh lakhs. The individuals earning income from the following sources can file ITR 1 Sahaj Form:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-30 ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Salaried person- Salary refers to the remuneration or consideration that a person receives for the services he or she has to render under the contract of employment. The Income Tax Act,1961 includes the following under the salary income</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Wages</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Pension</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Annuity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Advance salary paid</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Leave Encashment</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Fee, prerequisites, commission, profits besides or in lieu id the salary or wages</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Transferred balance in recognized provident fund</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Annual accretion to the recognized provident fund</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Central Government contribution or an employer contribution to Pension account as mentioned in Section 80 CCD of the Income Tax Act.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">One house property:</span>&nbsp;If the taxpayer is the owner of a property from which he or she is earning rent, the rent proceeds become taxable.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		However, if the taxpayer is using the owner of a property from which he or she is earning rent, the rent proceeds become taxable. However, if the taxpayer is using the property for running some business or profession the same would be taxable under the heading &ldquo;Income from business or profession&rdquo;.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Other sources (does not include income earned from winning lottery or racehorses)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Agricultural income (Upto to Rs. 5000)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'itr-1-return', 'Personal Tax Return Filing', 'Personal Tax Return Filing Free income tax Filing for salaried individuals and business persons. File ITR-1 to ITR-7 tax returns by importing Form 16 or Form 26AS documents on smartFilings.', 'Personal Tax Return Filing, Personal Tax Return Filing in vellore, smart filings, income tax india filing, income tax filing, income tax filing, tax filing, income tax return filing, it return filing, it filing, itr 1, itr 1 form, itr 1 filing, itr 1 meaning, itr 1 form download, itr 1 login, itr 1 download, itr 1 2 3 4 5 6 meaning, income tax itr 1, itr 1 and itr 4, itr 1 online, tr 1 to 7, itr 1 for salaried employees, itr 1 filing online, efiling itr 1, income tax itr 1 form, for individuals which itr form, itr1 pdf, itr form 1 pdf, 139 1 itr, itr form no 1, itr form 1 2 3 4, itr 1 xml file, itr form number 1, itr 1 and itr 2, itr 1 itr 2, tr 1 2 3, itr 1 return filing, tr 2 for which income, itr 1 format, income tax e filing itr 1, itr 1 for individual, income tax filing itr 1, itr 1 for salaried person, itr 1 computation format, filing type for itr 1, itr 1 return, income tax itr 1 download, meaning of itr1 itr2 itr3 itr4 itr5, income tax return online, itr 2 filling, itr 1 to 7 pdf, exempt income in itr 1, documents required for itr 1, itr form for interest income only, income from other sources itr 1, itr 1 form for ay 2020 21 pdf download, itr 1 online form, itr 1 income from other sources, itr 1 form filling online, wrong itr form filed, income tax return form itr 1, itr 1 for nri, itr 1 and 2, ill itr 1, professional tax deduction in itr 1, itr type 1, itr 1 form filling, itr 1 for which income, itr loan full form, itr 1 excel, itr 1 filled form example, about itr 1, itr 1 to 5, itr 1 2020, itr filing, itr 1 2, income tax itr 1 filing, itr 1 form download pdf, download itr 1 pdf, individual salaried itr form, xml file for itr 1, salaried class itr form, pre filled itr 1, itr 1 is applicable for, income tax itr 1 form download, form 1 itr, income tax return itr 1, itr 1 for pensioners,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL);
