(35, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-2 Return', 'Personal Tax Return Filing ITR-2 ', 'Income tax return filing for persons having DIN or owing private limited company shares.', 'Income tax return filing for persons having capital gains.', 'Income tax return filing for persons having foreign assets or foreign income.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 2 Form Filing</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 2 Form is an Important form income tax return form that is used by the Indian Citizens as well as the NRIs to file the return with the Income-tax department of India. The taxpayers who are not eligible to file ITR 1 can file ITR 1 to file the income tax returns. ITR 2 can be filed by the individuals and Hindu Undivided Families who have their income for the financial year through salary, pension, more than one property, income from capital gains, income from foreign assets, business or income from a profession as a partner and other sources that include lottery, Racehorses, legal gambling.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Also, an individual who is not eligible to file using ITR 1 as the income is exceeding Rs.50 Lakh can file ITR 2 Form.</p>\r\n', 488, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for persons having DIN or owing private limited company shares.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for persons having capital gains.</span>', 2488, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for persons having foreign assets or foreign income.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-28-05-pmITR-2.jpg', 1, 988, '<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 30px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Copy of the previous year&rsquo;s tax return</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Bank Statement</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		TDS Certificate</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Savings Certificate/ Deductions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Interest Statement that shows the interest that is paid throughout the year.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Balance sheet, P &amp; I, Account Statement, and other Audit reports wherever they are applicable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who can file Form ITR-2?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR form 2 can be filed by individuals and the HUF who are not eligible to file form ITR-1 receiving income from the &ldquo;profits and gains from business or profession&rdquo;. Thus persons having come from the following sources are eligible to file Form ITR 2:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-plus list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from Salary/Pension</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from House property ( can be from more than one house property)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from Capital gains</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from other sources (Lottery, bets on horses, and other gambling)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Foreign Assets/Foreign Income</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Agricultural income more than Rs.5000</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		A resident is not an ordinary resident and an NRI.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Also, a director of any company and an individual who is invested in unlisted equity shares of a company should file their returns in ITR-2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is not eligible to file Form ITR-2?</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-plus list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Any individual or Hindu Undivided Family with income that is fully or partially earned from the business or profession.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Individuals that are eligible to file ITR 1 Form.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Individuals who are partners in a Partnership Firm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'itr-2-return', 'Personal Tax Return Filing ITR-2', 'Personal Tax Return Filing ITR-2 Free income tax Filing for salaried individuals and business persons. File ITR-1 to ITR-7 tax returns by importing Form 16 or Form 26AS documents on smartFilings.', 'Personal Tax Return Filing ITR-2, income tax india efiling, income tax efiling, income tax filing, tax filing, income tax return filing, it return filing, it filing, Personal Tax Return Filing in vellore, smart filings, itr 2, itr 2 form, itr 2 filing, itr 2 income tax, itr 2 xml file, itr 2 online filing, itr 2 xml, itr 2 for, income tax itr 2, itr 2 capital gains, itr3 and itr 4, itr filing 2.0, file itr 2 online, itr form 1 2 3 4, xml file for itr 2, itr 2 is for, itr 1 and itr 2, xml for itr 2, itr 1 itr 2, itr 1 2 3, re filled itr 2 form, itr 2 for which income, itr 2 format, itr 2 excel, itr 2 for nri, itr 2 eligibility, about itr 2, itr 2 details, meaning of itr1 itr2 itr3 itr4 itr5, itr 2 filling, itr 2 for salaried employees, agriculture income in itr 2, income tax form itr 2, form 2 itr, itr 1 and 2, fill itr 2 form online, itr form no 2, itr form number 2, itr 1 form filling, itr 2 online, itr 2 agriculture income, itr 2 form for nri, itr 1 2, income tax filing itr 2, itr 2 income tax return form, itr2 filling, filing of itr 2, online itr 2 filing, file itr with 2 form 16, itr 2 return filing, itr type 2, itr 2 e filing, exempt income in itr 2, tds2 in itr, itr 2 not available online, filling itr2, itr form for 2 house property, itr 2 filing step by step, itr 2 income from other sources, two house property itr form, itr 2 for non resident, itr form for two house property, itr for 2 house property, itr 2 requirements, online filing of itr 2, itr 2 filing help, income tax e filing itr 2, itr 2 form online, itr 2 meaning, itr2 xml format, itr 2 filing form,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(36, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-3 Return', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-3', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.25 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.50 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of Rs.20 lakhs to Rs.100 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 3 Form Filing</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 3 Form is applicable for the individuals and Hindu Undivided Families that earn profit and gains from business or profession.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	If the individual or the Hindu undivided family is having an income as a partner of a partnership firm that is carrying out business then ITR-3 cannot be filed as in such cases the individual is required to file ITR-2.</p>\r\n', 2899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.50 lakhs.</span>', 9899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of Rs.20 lakhs to Rs.100 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-28-59-pmITR-3.jpg', 1, 5899, '<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 3 Form can be filed either offline or online:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">Offline:</span>&nbsp;The returns can be furnished in a paper format through a bar-coded return.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 600;\">Online:</span>&nbsp;The returns can be furnished electronically using the Digital Signature Certificate. This data can be transmitted after submitting the verification of the return.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The assessee must have two print copies of the ITR 3 Form when he is filing the returns online.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Electronic returns can be filed when:</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The assessee is a resident of India or if the signing authority is located outside India.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The assessees with more than Rs.5 lakh total income are required to furnish the returns electronically.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Assessees that are claiming relief under Section 90, 90A,91 for whom the schedule FSI and Schedule TR that applies must file the returns electronically.</p>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Instructions to be followed while filing ITR 3 Form</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Sections mentioned above will have to be addressed in the Form. But here is the list of important instructions that are to be followed while filing the ITR 3 Form:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-30 ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		If in case the Schedule is not applicable to the assessee, then the assessee has to just put -NA-</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		In case if there is no figure to denote, mention Nil.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		If there is a negative balance and you are writing it against a profit column then the&quot; - &quot; sign needs to be added before the figure.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Round off the figures to the nearest one rupee.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The total income or the payable loss should be rounded off to the nearest multiple of Rs.10.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The Section in Part A needs to be filled after that 23 schedules are to be filled in Part B, Finally, you need to verify the document.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'itr-3-return', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-3', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-3 File income tax return for your business. smartFilings is an Income Tax Return Intermediary Authorized to file business tax returns.', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-3, ITR-3 in vellore, smart filings, income tax efiling, income tax filing, business tax return filing, business tax filing, company tax return filing, llp tax return filing, proprietorship tax return filing, partnership firm tax return filing, itr 3, itr 3 means, itr 3 form, itr 3 download, itr 3 income tax, itr 1 2 3 4 5 6 meaning, itr 3 filing, itr 3 form download, itr 1 2 3 4 means, download itr 3, itr3 for, itr 3 and itr 4, form itr 3, itr 3 xml, itr form 3 download, itr 3 is for, itr form 1 2 3 4, itr 3 for which income, itr 3 online filing, itr 1 2 3, itr 3 presumptive income, file itr 3 online, itr 3 online, itr3 xml file, itr 3 filing online, meaning of itr1 itr2 itr3 itr4 itr5, download itr for last 3 years, want to file itr for last 3 years, file itr 3, form 3 itr, itr 3 filling, agriculture income in itr 3, itr 3 return filing, itr 3 details, last 3 years itr, income tax itr 3 download, itr form no 3, download last 3 years itr, itr 3 xml format, xml file for itr 3, itr 3 xml file download, documents required for filing itr 3, itr 3 for salaried person, download itr 3 form, itr 3 filing fees, 3 years itr, download itr 3 pdf, income tax return itr 3, itr 3 download excel format, itr 3 balance sheet, itr for last 3 years, income tax form itr 3, itr form 1 2 3 4 5 means, itr3 form pdf, itr 3 income tax form download, itr form 3 filing, about itr 3, itr last 3 years, online itr 3 filing, xml for itr 3, itr 3 for presumptive income, itr of last 3 years, itr 3 excel,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(37, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-4 Return', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-4', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.25 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 4 Form Filing</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Form ITR 4 is filed by the taxpayers who have opted for the Presumptive Taxation Scheme under Section 44D, 44DA, 44AE of the Income Tax Act,1961. But this is subject to the business turnover limit i.e in case if the turnover is exceeding Rs.2 crore then the taxpayer is required to file ITR 3 Form.</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"lead\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 400;\">\r\n	What is Presumptive Taxation in Scheme?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Presumptive Taxation Scheme is a scheme that exempts small taxpayers from maintaining the books of accounts.</p>\r\n', 2899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', 9899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-29-53-pmITR-4.jpg', 1, 5899, '<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR-4 can be submitted both online and offline as well.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	Offline</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify lead m-b-5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 5px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The following individuals can file offline form:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Individuals at the age of 80 years or more</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The individual&#39;s income is less than Rs.5 Lakh and he does not have to claim a refund in the income tax return</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify lead m-b-5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 5px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 4 can be filed offline :</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		By furnishing a return in a physical paper form</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		By furnishing a bar-coded return (An acknowledgment will be issued at the time of submission of the physical paper return)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	Online/Electronically</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		By furnishing the return digitally using the digital signature.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		By transmitting the data electronically and then submitting the verification of the return made in Form ITR-V.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	If the ITR-4 Form is under digital signature then an acknowledgment will be sent to the registered email id.</p>\r\n', '<h2 id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is Eligible to file Form ITR 4?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Individuals whose income comes from the following sources have to file ITR 4 Form:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-plus list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Business Income under Section 44AD/Section 44AE.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from a profession as per Section 44ADA.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income up to Rs. 50 lakh from Salary or Pension.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income up to Rs. 50 lakh from One house property (that does not include the brought forward loss o loss that is to be brought forward under this head)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Income from other sources up to Rs.50 lakh (does not include winning from lottery or horse races)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Form ITR 4 can also be filed by the freelancers if the income is not exceeding Rs.50 lakh.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 id=\"nav_link_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is not eligible for ITR 4 Form?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The following individuals need to file ITR-4:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-plus list-icon-colored text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Holds Directorship in a company</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Holds any unlisted equity shares at any time during the previous year</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has assets/financial interest in an entity outside India</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has signing authority in any account outside India</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has income from a source located outside India</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has profits from a business or profession which is not required to be computed under sections 44AD, 44ADA, or 44AE, like income from a speculative business, commission, brokerage, etc.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Makes Capital Gains</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has income from more than one house property</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has income under the head &quot;other sources&quot; from winning the lottery, horse races, income taxable at special rates u/s 115BBDA or 115BBE</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has income which is to be apportioned under the provisions of Section 5A</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has agricultural income exceeding INR 5,000</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has any brought forward loss or loss which is to be carried forward under any income head</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has loss under &ldquo;income from other sources&rdquo;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has a claim of relief under Sections 90, 90A or 91</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has any deduction claim under Section 57 (except deduction relating to family pension)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has claim of tax credit which has been deducted at source in the hands of another person</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Has joint ownership in house property (inserted in AY 20-21).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'itr-4-return', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-4', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-4 File income tax return for your business. smartFilings is an Income Tax Return Intermediary Authorized to file business tax returns.', 'Business Tax Return Filing ITR-4, income tax efiling, income tax filing, business tax return filing, business tax filing, company tax return filing, llp tax return filing, proprietorship tax return filing, partnership firm tax return filing, Business Tax Return Filing ITR-4 in vellore, smart filings, itr 4, itr 4 form, itr 4 meaning, itr 4 income tax, itr 4 download, itr 1 2 3 4 5 6 meaning, itr 4 filing, itr type 4, itr 1 and itr 4, itr for presumptive income, 44ada itr form, itr 3 and itr 4, itr 4 form download, itr 4 for, itr4s, itr 4 pdf, itr 4 computation format in excel, itr 4 is for, itr form 1 2 3 4, itr4 meaning, tr form for presumptive income, agriculture income in itr 4, itr 4 capital gain, itr 4 presumptive income, income tax return itr 4, meaning of itr1 itr2 itr3 itr4 itr5, capital gain in itr 4, itr 4 details, itr 4 return filing, itr 4 online, itr 4 computation format, itr form no 4, balance sheet format in excel for itr 4, itr form 4 pdf, itr form number 4, itr 4 login, itr 4 filling, about itr 4, itr form 4 download, itr 4 excel format calculation, form 4 itr, itr 44ada, balance sheet for itr 4, itr 4 44ad, file itr 4 online, file itr 4, e filing itr 4, itr 4 return, itr 1 and 4, sample itr 4 filled form, tr 4 for freelancer, itr 5 and itr 7, ncome tax itr 4 download, itr 4 nil return, tr 4 e filing, balance sheet format for itr 4, partnership firm can file itr 4,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(38, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-5 Return', 'Annual Compliance - Partnership Firm - ITR-5', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 5 Form Filing</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The taxpayers are supposed to file the Income Tax returns based on the income that is earned by them in the financial year and the kind of entity that it falls under. ITR 5 Form filing is to be done by the Association of Persons, Limited Liability Partnerships, Body of Individuals, Estates of the deceased, Artificial judicial person, business trust, estates of the insolvent, business trust, and investment fund.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	This article is a comprehensive guide you can refer to while filing the Income Tax returns in Form 5.</p>\r\n', 9899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', 13899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-30-53-pmITR-5.jpg', 1, 11899, '<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Details of recognition as a start-up by DPIIT</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Declaration Details filed in Form-2</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Information about the partnership firms where an individual is a partner</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Bifurcation of donations into cash and non-cash mode of payment.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Information on turnover and the gross receipts reported for GST.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is Eligible to file ITR 5 Form?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; letter-spacing: 0px;\">\r\n	ITR 5 can be filed by the following people :</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		A firm</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		A Limited Liability Partnership</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Association of Persons</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Body of Individuals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Artificial Judicial Persons that are referred to in Section 2 (31) (vii)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The local authority that is referred to in Section 160(1) (ii) or 160 (1) (iv)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Cooperative Society</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Societies that are registered under Societies Registration Act, 1860 or under any state law trust ( except the trusts that are eligible for ITR 7 Form Filing)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Estate of the deceased person</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Business trust referred to in Section 139 (4E)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Investment fund referred to in Section 139 (4F)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is not eligible to file Form ITR 5?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	An individual who has to file income tax returns under the Section 139 (4A) or 139 (4D) cannot file ITR 5 Form.</p>\r\n', 'itr-5-return', 'Annual Compliance - Partnership Firm - ITR-5', 'Annual Compliance - Partnership Firm - ITR-5 File income tax return. smartFilings is an Income Tax Return Intermediary Authorized to file tax returns.', 'Annual Compliance - Partnership Firm - ITR-5, income tax efiling, income tax filing, business tax return filing, business tax filing, company tax return filing, llp tax return filing, proprietorship tax return filing, partnership firm tax return filing, ITR filing vellore, smart filings, itr 1 2 3 4 5 6 meaning, meaning of itr1 itr2 itr3 itr4 itr5, itr 5 and itr 7, itr 5, itr 5 form, itr 5 meaning, itr 5 download, itr 5 income tax, itr 5 online filing, itr 5 for partnership firm, itr 5 applicability, my income is below 5 lakhs should i file itr, itr 5 for, itr 5 is for, itr 5 form download, itr 5 acknowledgement, itr below 5 lakhs income, itr 1 to 5, itr 5 filing, income tax itr 5, itr 5 xml file download, itr filing below 5 lakhs, itr for income less than 5 lakhs, form 5 itr, itr filing for income less than 5 lakhs, itr 5 login, itr 5 for trust, income tax itr 5 download,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(39, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-6 Return', 'Annual Compliance - Company - ITR-6', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 42px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 6 Filing Form</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 6 Form is to be furnished by the Companies to e-file the income tax returns if they are not claiming exemption under Section 11 of the Income Tax Act 1961. Under the Income-tax Rules, the Companies that can claim an exemption under section 11 are those that have income from the property that is held for the charitable or religious person.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Hence, ITR 6 is to be filed by the companies that do not claim an exemption under section 11.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px; line-height: 1.68421em; font-size: 1.35714em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	Efiling audit reports</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	If in case the assessee is liable for the audit u/s 44AB and the accountant has audited the accounts, then the details of the audit report, the auditor along with the date of furnishing is to be sent to the department electronically.</p>\r\n', 9899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', 15899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-31-44-pmITR-6.jpg', 1, 12899, '<p>\r\n	No annexures required</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	No document (including TDS certificate) should be attached with this return form while filing ITR-6.Taxpayers are advised to match the taxes deducted/collected/paid by or on behalf of them with their Tax Credit Statement Form 26AS</p>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is eligible to file ITR 6 Form?</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		ITR 6 Form is to be filed by every company irrespective of its structure registered under the Companies Act 2013 or the earlier Companies Act 1956. However, the companies whose source of income comes from the property that is held for religious or charitable purposes are not required to file ITR 6 Form.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		If the sales, turnover, or gross receipts are more than Rs.1 crore in the preceding financial year the entity must get the accounts audited from a certified Chartered Accountant.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Who is not eligible to file ITR 6 Form?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The companies who have sources of income from religious or charitable organizations can seek exemption under Section 11. In simpler words, an entity that is seeking exemption under Section 11 should not file ITR 6 Form.</p>\r\n', 'itr-6-return', 'Annual Compliance - Company - ITR-6', 'File income tax return smartFilings is an Income Tax Return Intermediary Authorized to file tax returns.', 'Annual Compliance - Company - ITR-6, income tax efiling, income tax filing, business tax return filing, business tax filing, company tax return filing, llp tax return filing, proprietorship tax return filing, partnership firm tax return filing, Annual Compliance filing in vellore, smart filings, itr 1 2 3 4 5 6 meaning, itr 6, itr 6 form, itr 6 download, itr 6 income tax, download itr 6, itr 6 form download, itr 6 applicability, tr 6 filing, itr 6 for,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL);
