(40, 1, 16, '', 'ITR-7 Return', 'ITR-7 Return Filing', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of More than Rs.10 lakhs.', 'Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	ITR 7 Form Filing</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 7 Form filing is done by the companies who service the income from the properties that are of charitable or religious purposes. Properties that are held under the trusts or legal obligation in parts or even wholly are included in the category.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR taxpayers can fill the ITR 7 Forms by providing the returns through a bard coded form, physical paperback forms, or the digital signature mode, or the submission of return verification through ITR Form V.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	ITR 7 Form is a file when the person and the companies fall under section 139(4A) or Section 139 (4B) or Section 139 (4C) or Section 139(4D).</p>\r\n', 9899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of less than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.10 lakhs.</span>', 15899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Income tax return filing for a taxpayer with taxable income of more than Rs.25 lakhs.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-32-31-pmITR-7.jpg', 1, 12899, 'No annexures required<br />\r\nNo document (including TDS certificate) should be attached with this return form while filing ITR-7.<br />\r\nTaxpayers are advised to match the taxes deducted/collected/paid by or on behalf of them with their Tax Credit Statement Form 26AS.<br />\r\nE-filing audit reports I<br />\r\nf the assessee is liable for Audit u/s 44AB and the accounts have been audited by an accountant, the details of such audit report along with the date of furnishing it to the department has to be filled under the head &ldquo;Audit Information.', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center;\">\r\n	Sequence for filing ITR 7 Form</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px;\">\r\n	What is the sequence for filing ITR 7 Form?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Income Tax Department has advised the assessees to follow the sequence that is mentioned below while filing the Income Tax return.</p>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Part A</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Part B</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Schedules</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Verification.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Enter the information required in the verification document and strike out the which is not applicable and this verification must be digitally signed before furnishing the final return.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	It is necessary for the person signing to mention his designation in the entity on behalf of whom the return is being filed.</p>\r\n', 'itr-7-return', 'ITR-7 Return Filing', 'File income tax return smartFilings is an Income Tax Return Intermediary Authorized to file tax returns.', 'ITR-7 Return Filing, income tax efiling, income tax filing, business tax return filing, business tax filing, company tax return filing, llp tax return filing, proprietorship tax return filing, partnership firm tax return filing, itr 7, itr 7 form, itr 1 to 7, itr 7 means, itr 7 applicability, itr 7 pdf, itr 7 download, itr 7 income tax, itr 1 to 7 pdf, itr 7 of income tax act, itr 5 and itr 7, ITR filing in vellore, smart filings,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(41, 1, 16, '', 'Income Tax Notice', 'Income Tax Notice Response', 'Consultation for income tax notice handling and response from a Tax Expert.', 'Consultation for income tax notice response from a Tax Expert and revised return filing.', 'Consultation for income tax notice response from a Tax Expert, revised return filing and submission of documents requested.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	Income Tax Notice</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Income Tax Department sends the notices for various reasons like not filing the income tax returns, any defect while filing the returns, or other instances where the tax department is requiring any additional documents or information.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Nothing is frightening or alarming about the notice that is received. But the taxpayer has to first understand the notice, the nature of the notice, the requestor&#39;s order in the notice, and take steps to comply.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	SmartFilings offers a comprehensive suite of services for families and businesses to help them in maintaining the compliances. In case an income tax notice is received get in touch with the Tax Expert at IndiaFilings to understand the income tax notice and determine a course of action.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Let us understand the various types of notices or intimations issued by the Income Tax Department.</p>\r\n', 488, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Consultation for income tax notice handling and response from a Tax Expert.</span>', '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Consultation for income tax notice response from a Tax Expert and revised return filing.</span>', 4899, '<span style=\"color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">Consultation for income tax notice response from a Tax Expert, revised return filing and submission of documents requested.</span>', '02-02-2022-12-33-24-pmincome-tax-help.jpg', 1, 1899, '<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-arrow list-icon-colored text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		The Income Tax Notice copy.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Proof of Income source such as (Part B ) of Form 16, Salary receipts, etc.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		TDS certificates, Form 16 (Part A)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Investment Proof if they are applicable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Service of Income Tax Notice</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The Income Tax Act,1961 has laid down the law for the service of a notice, summons, order, or any other communication by delivering or transmitting a copy to the person in any method that is sanctioned under the Act. Here are the various ways in which the Income Tax Notice is served.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: 600;\">Recipient of the Notice:&nbsp;</span>Income Tax Notices are directly addressed to the individual but if they are meant for a minor they are addressed to the guardian Incorrect description of the assessee is usually rectifiable but in case of scenarios where the status of the assessee is entangled with the identity of the assessee, the name mentioned on the face of the return may become material.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: 600;\">Service by Post:&nbsp;</span>Service of the income tax notice can be processed through a registered post. Section 27 of the General Clauses Act 1897, specifies that the service is to be initiated by properly addressing, pre-paying, and posting by a registered post a letter that contains the document. This delivery can be made to the address, an employee, agent, or any other authorized person.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: 600;\">Service by Affixture:&nbsp;</span>In case a defendant refuses to sign the acknowledgment or where the officer is not able to find the defendant, then the office has to affix a copy of the summons or notice or requisition order on the outer door or any other noticeable part of the residence where the defendant is residing or pursuing the business activities.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: 600;\">HUFs and the Partnership Firm:&nbsp;</span>If the officer discovers the total partition of any HUF it may be recorded by the assessing officer and the notices can be served on the person who was the manager of the HUF. If the concerned person is deceased then the notice will be served to all adults who were firm or other Association of Persons, notices concerning the income of the firm or the association may be served on any personnel who were former partners or the members of the association that is assessed to taxation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<span class=\"t_u\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: 600;\">Closed Business:&nbsp;</span>In case of closed business, the assessing officer has to serve as a notice on the person whose income is subject to assessment. In the case of the firm or an association of persons a notice will be served to any of the members who have been a part of the firm during discontinuation. Concerning a company, the notice will be served on the principal officer or the Director.</p>\r\n', 'income-tax-notice', 'Income Tax Notice Response', 'Income tax notice can be sent by the income tax department for various reasons like not filing tax return, filing of tax return with incorrect information or other reasons. smartFilings provides tax expert support to help you understand and respond to income tax notices.', 'Income Tax Notice Response, Income tax notice, tax notice, tax notice help, Income Tax Notice in vellore, section 148 of income tax act, income tax notification, income tax latest notification, sec 148 of income tax act, income tax notification 2020, 148 of income tax act, income tax notification 2021, section 156 of income tax act, notice under section 148, high value transactions notice, income tax notice for cash deposits 2021, sec 143 of income tax act, received income tax notice for mismatch in income with form 26as, outstanding demand in income tax, income tax section 148, 148 income tax, income tax notice on property purchase, 143 1 itr, response to outstanding demand income tax, income tax demand notice, income tax notice for cash deposits 2020, income tax new notification, notice from income tax department, income tax outstanding demand, 143 1 a income tax, 143 income tax, income tax notice of assessment, section 148 of income tax, income tax notice for cash transaction, income tax scrutiny notice, itr notice, 143 of income tax act, notice of demand under section 156, latest income tax notice of assessment, income tax notice for car purchase, income tax notice list, notice us 148, income tax notice of registration, personal income tax bill notice, section 292bb of income tax act, section 148 of income tax act 1961, section 156 income tax act, income tax notice for not filing return, notice to file return of income for complete year, income tax outstanding demand status, notice under section 154 of income tax act 1961, notice of demand income tax, section 147 notice, 1431a demand notice, income tax notification latest, notice under section 245, income tax notice for cash deposits, notice under income tax act, outstanding tax demand, notice under section 148 income tax act, income tax notice after death, income tax notice us 148, income tax notice high value transaction, income tax recent notification, income tax 154 notice, 154 notice income tax, income tax notice for high value transaction, income tax notice under section 148, 148 income tax notice, 143 notice income tax, show cause notice under income tax act, income tax notice for senior citizens, compliance notice income tax, 154 income tax notice, interest on income tax demand, section 148 of the income tax act 1961, income tax return notice of assessment, income tax notice 148, income tax notification today, itr demand notice, outstanding demand of income tax, income tax due notice, notice 148 of income tax act, income tax notice online, income tax 148 notice, section 156 of income tax act 1961, income notice of assessment, 156 income tax act, income tax new notification 2021, assessment notice income tax, new notification of income tax, non filing income tax notice, income tax notice of assessment, income tax notice for cash withdrawal, income tax notice under section 154, income tax return notice, latest notification of income tax department, 143 1 a income tax section, show cause notice income tax, income tax notice under section 245, personal income tax notice of assessment, demand notice from income tax department, smart filings, ', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(42, 1, 16, '', 'TDS Return', 'TDS Return Filing', 'TDS return filing for one quarter', 'TDS return filing for two quarters.', 'TDS return filing for four quarter.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	TDS Return Filing</h1>\r\n<h2 class=\"lead\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 400;\">\r\n	What is TDS return filing?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Apart from depositing the tax the deductor also has to do TDS return filing. TDS return filing is a quarterly statement that is to be given to the Income Tax department. It is necessary to submit the TDS returns on time. TDS return filing can be done completely online. Once the TDS returns are submitted the details will come up on Form 26 AS. While filing the TDS returns the various details to be mentioned are:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0 p-l-15\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		PAN of the deductor and the deductee.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Amount of tax that is paid to the government</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		TDS challan information</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Others, if any.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 1499, 'TDS Return Filing For One Quarter', 'TDS Return Filing For Two Quarters.', 4899, 'TDS Return Filing For Four Quarter.', '02-02-2022-12-34-31-pmtds-return.jpg', 1, 2499, '<div>\r\n	Form 16:<br />\r\n	CHECK THESE OUT.<br />\r\n	Salary slips For salaried taxpayers, it is important to keep the salary slip ready.<br />\r\n	Form 26AS:<br />\r\n	Form 16A<br />\r\n	PAN card:<br />\r\n	Aadhaar card:<br />\r\n	Deductions under Section 80D to 80U:<br />\r\n	Capital Gain Statement:</div>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	What is TDS?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Tax deducted at source or TDS is the tax that is collected by the Government of India at the time when a transaction takes place. Here, in this case, the tax is to be deducted at the time the money is credited to the payee&#39;s account or at the time of payment whichever happens earlier.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	In this case of salary payment or the life insurance policy, the tax is deducted at the time when the payment is done. The deductor is required to deposit this amount with the Income Tax Department. Through TDS a portion of the tax is paid directly to the Income Tax Department. The Tax is deducted usually over a range of 10%.</p>\r\n', 'tds-return', 'TDS Return Filing', 'File TDS return online through smartFilings with TDS Expert Support just Rs 999. Know how to file TDS return online without software. TDS return is a quarterly statement to be given to the I-T department.', 'TDS Return Filing, TDS return filing in vellore, tds filing, tds return, tds software, tds return,tds return due dates, file tcs return, tds return filing, gstr 7, tds filing, form 26q, form 27q, form 24q, e tds, tds e filing, tcs return, 27eq, 26q tds, 24q tds, tds due dates, form 27eq, tds return form, tds return filing online, tds filing due dates, tds return filing dates, tds quarterly return due dates, tds return filing due dates, file tcs return online, tds return utility, tcs return form, 27q tds, 27eq tds, tcs return filing, form 27q tds, tds form 26q, tds return form 26q, 24q and 26q, online tds return, gst tds return, income tax tds refund, tds quarterly return, tds return software, tds online filing, income tax tds return, tds return preparation utility, tds filing software, form 27a tds, tds refund form 16, late filing of tds return, form 24q tds, tds refund online, itr form 26as, nsdl tds utility, gst tcs return, tds revised return, tcs return form 27eq, form 27eq tds, form 27q online, tds return filing utility, tcs filing, 27eq form, 234e tds, form 26q download, tds return filing software, password for tds return acknowledgement, 24q tds return, e filing tds return, efiling tds, tds return for salary, ds filing utility, e tds return, tds preparation utility, tds on gst return, tds return acknowledgement password, tds quarterly return filing, 27a tds, gstr 7 form, itr tds, tds payment dates, tds return 26q, tds return download, nsdl tds software, tds deposit due dates, etds filing due dates, salary tds form, e tds software, apply for tds, statement of tds, 194j income tax return form, form for tcs return, tds returns and due dates, return preparation utility, gstr 7 return, form 24q and 26q, tcs return utility, tds submission, tds nil return filing, documents required for tds return, nsdl tds return utility, tds refund form, tds gst return, 26q and 24q, form 27eq tcs, tds return acknowledgement, tds return utility download, form 24q income tax, tds annual return, income tax tds filing, form no 27eq, itr tds refund, form no 26q, tds return 27q, gstr 7 filing, tcs filing form, tds return section, form 26q pdf, tds 24q and 26q, form gstr 7, tds return processing time, tds return offline utility, tds tcs return, tds filing forms, gstr 07, e filing tds online, about tds return, tds return software free download full version, form 24q pdf, file tds return on traces, tds return password, tds quarterly filing, 27q return, tds return details, tds deducted but return not filed, form 27q for sale of property online, tcs return filing form, 24q return, tds return full form, 24q income tax, 24q 26q, tcs return in gst, nsdl return preparation utility, non filing of tds return, tds return under gst, tds return software price, form 27q in tds, 26q income tax, form 27q pdf, form 24q online, 27q tds return, tds and tcs due dates, form 26q income tax, tds return form 27q, download 26q from traces, e tds return preparation utility, e return file validation utility, tds file password, tds fill, tds return in gst, tds fvu version, free tds return software, tds return form 24q, smart filings,', 1, 1, 1, '', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL),
(43, 1, 16, '', 'Form 16', 'Form 16 Issuance', 'For businesses having 1 - 25 employees. Includes TDS Filing for Q4 with Annexure II, Form 16 issuance and ITR-1 filing for employees.', 'For businesses having 26 - 100 employees. Includes TDS Filing for Q4 with Annexure II, Form 16 issuance and ITR-1 filing for employees.', 'For businesses having 101 - 500 employees. Includes TDS Filing for Q4 with Annexure II, Form 16 issuance and ITR-1 filing for employees.', '<h1 class=\"text-center\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.31818em; font-size: 3.14286em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	Form 16 Issuance to Employees</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Form 16 is a certificate that employers issue to their employees. It is a validation that the TDS has been deducted and deposited with the government authorities on behalf of the employee of the organization.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Form 16 gives a detailed summary of the salary paid to the employees and the deducted TDS. TDS Form 16 contains all the information that an individual needs to prepare and file the income tax return.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The employers are required to issue a Salary TDS certificate every year on or before the 15th of June of the coming year immediately after the financial year in which the tax is deducted. There are two components of Form 16 Part A and Part B. If an individual loses Form 16 he can request a duplicate Form from the employer.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	IndiaFilings can help you manage TDS compliance online. Our TDS experts will help you file all the TDS returns pay any overdue TDS deposits and also the issuance of Form 16 to the employees.</p>\r\n', 200, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		1 - 25 Employees</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		4th Quarter TDS Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Annexure II Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Form 16 Generation &amp; Issuance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border: none; line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		ITR-1 Filing for Employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		26 - 100 Employees</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		4th Quarter TDS Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Annexure II Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Form 16 Generation &amp; Issuance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border: none; line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		ITR-1 Filing for Employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 300, '<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px 40px; display: table; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; text-align: center;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		101 - 500 Employees</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		4th Quarter TDS Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Annexure II Filing or Verification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 235); line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		Form 16 Generation &amp; Issuance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; border: none; line-height: 42px;\">\r\n		ITR-1 Filing for Employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '02-02-2022-12-35-14-pmform-16.jpg', 1, 250, '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Structure of Form 16</h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Part A of Form 16</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	It provides the details of the TDS that is deducted and deposited. This form can be generated by the employers through the TRACES portal.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The employer must verify the contents before issuing the certificate. Here are a few components of Part A of the salary TDS certificate.</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Name and address of the employer</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		TAN and PAN of employer</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		PAN of the employee</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Summary of tax deducted and deposited quarterly, which is certified by the employer.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Part B of Form 16</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	It is an annexure to Part A, Part B is prepared by the employer for its employees and it contains details of the breakup of the salary deductions approved under Chapter VI-A. In case of a job change in one financial year, Form 16 should be obtained by both employers. Some of the components of Part B are:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul_f_f ul_f_f_decimal text-justify p-l-30 m-b-30\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; list-style: decimal; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 30px !important; padding-left: 30px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Detailed breakup of salary</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Detailed breakup of exempted allowances under Section 10</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 5px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deductions that are allowed under Income Tax Act (Under Chapter VIA)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 12px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.5em; font-size: 1.78571em; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251);\">\r\n	Here is the list of deductions</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"p-l-15 ul_f_f list-icon list-icon-check list-icon-colored text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px; background-color: rgb(247, 249, 251); margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for life insurance premium paid, contribution to PPF, etc. under Section 80C</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for contribution to pension funds under Section 80CC</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for employee&#39;s contribution to a pension scheme under Section 80CCD(1)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for taxpayer&#39;s self contribution to a notified pension scheme under Section 80CCD(1B)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for employer&#39;s contribution to a pension scheme under Section 80CCD(2)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for health insurance premium paid under Section 80D</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for interest paid on loan taken for higher education under Section 80E</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for donations made under Section 80G</li>\r\n	<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px 20px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		Deduction for interest income on savings account under Section 80TTA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2 class=\"text-center\" id=\"nav_link_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); letter-spacing: 0.5px; font-size: 2.35714em; line-height: 1.36364em; font-weight: 500; text-align: center;\">\r\n	TDS on Salary</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	TDS is calculated on the income tax rates that are prescribed for the financial year in which the payment of the employee is made. An individual responsible for paying the taxes can increase or decrease the amount that is deducted based on any adjustments in the previous deficiency or excess deduction.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	The total amount of the TDs will be determined by the following elements:</p>\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 1110px; overflow-x: auto; color: rgb(72, 72, 72); font-family: Nunito, sans-serif; font-size: 14.08px;\">\r\n	<table class=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; width: 1110px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41);\">\r\n		<thead style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n		</thead>\r\n		<tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n			<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Exemption Limit</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Leave Encashment</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Notified Allowances</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					House rate allowance</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Perquisites</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Donation by employees under 80G</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Other deductions</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Bonus or incentives</td>\r\n				<td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0.75rem; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(222, 226, 230) rgb(236, 236, 236) rgb(236, 236, 236); vertical-align: top;\">\r\n					Estimated Salary</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1rem; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	If an individual is employed by more than one employer during a financial year then tax will be deducted on the aggregate salary by one of the employers as chosen by the employee by submitting information in Form 12B.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify m-b-0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14.08px; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(119, 119, 119); font-family: Poppins, sans-serif; margin-bottom: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;\">\r\n	Thus if an employee has more than one employer in a financial year then he is required to furnish information in Form 12 B to one of the employers. Once Form 12B is submitted it becomes an obligation for the employer to deduct TDS.</p>\r\n', 'form-16', 'Form 16 Issuance', 'Learn about what is Form 16? find how to download form 16 with its meaning & format online at smartFilings. Form 16 is the certificate of TDS deducted from salary.', 'Form 16 Issuance, Salary TDS certificate, Form 16, Form 16A, Form 16B, Form 16 Part A, TDS Form 16,